author: Warhammer
description:
Through the ruins of a shattered chapel, Saint Celestine descends like an answered prayer, her golden armour gleaming as a symbol of the Emperor’s grace and wrath.

Celestine the Living Saint is captured in breathtaking, reverent detail—a tribute to the legendary figure who inspires armies across the galaxy. Every element of the statue has been meticulously designed to embody Saint Celestine’s awe-inspiring power and grace.

This Limited Edition 1:6 scale collectible statue of Saint Celestine is an artifact of the Adepta Sororitas’ unwavering faith. With unparalleled detail and accuracy, this rendition of Celestine will be a striking addition to any collection, honouring the Living Saint’s divine splendour with artistry that
captures the essence of her glory and power.

Pre-order: https://www.wetanz.com/celestine-the-living-saint

COMING SOON
Soon to be joining this epic series of collectibles is Skragrott the Loonking, from Warhammer Age of Sigmar. View the range: https://www.wetanz
title: Warhammer 40,000 | Celestine the Living Saint, 1:6 Scale Limited Edition Statue, byWētā Workshop

author: Warhammer
description:
What flavour Seraphon is your favourite; maybe it's the jungle dwelling Coalesced or the celestial Starborne flying around in their ziggurat ships. Either way, today, Jake will show you some quick and colourful ways to get your Seraphon painted and ready to take part in the great plan. 
Here’s a list of the paints we used in today’s video:

Contrast:
Aethermatic Blue 
Aggaros Dunes 
Apothecary White
Baal Red
Basilicanum Grey
Dreadful Visage
Flesh Tearers Red
Leviadon Blue 
Magmadroth Flame 
Magos Purple
Stormfiend

Base:
Caliban Green
Corax White

Layer:
Fenrisian Grey 
Fire Dragon Bright 
Kislev Flesh
Russ Grey 
Skarsnik Green
White Scar
Wild Rider Red

Shade:
Drakenhof Nightshade 
Seraphim Sepia 
Soulblight Grey

Technical:
Contrast Medium

Brushes:
M layer
M shade
s dry 
If you're new to painting, our Citadel Colour Painting Essentials playlist hosts an array of beginner-friendly videos to help you get started.
